This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, which are both covered by the Computer Science sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel architecture for jointly learning to label sentences and tokens, which involves using attention mechanisms and explicit supervision for composing sentence-level representations. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), as these fields often involve similar techniques for learning and processing complex data structures.
